items.name: SS Command Tool
items.description:
Toggles various dino orders

Press "Control" to choose any mode or "Right Click" to cycle modes.

items.name: SS Construction Tool
items.description:
Gives extra slots on screen so that you can build more structures using key bindings at one time!

Press "Control" to switch tiers

items.name: SS Euthanasia Gun
items.description: Kills tamed dinos instantly. You can right click to mark dino for death then left click to confirm kill

items.name: SS Inventory Assistant
items.description:
Will clean your inventory.

Left click to open UI, right click to toggle on & off quickly.

items.name: SS Personal Teleporter
items.description:
- Left click to teleport
- Right Click to drop a beacon
- Uses Element Shards as ammo

items.name: SS Pillarator
items.description: Allows you to change or copy the settings of SS Dynamic Pillars. Left click to open UI, right click to save. Left clicking with a saved setting will apply those settings. Right click again to clear saved settings.

items.name: SS Remote
items.description:
- Turn things on/off & open/close doors
- Right click to toggle mode

items.name: SS Demo Gun
items.description:
- Fire to pick up or demolish items
- Right click to toggle mode between pick up and demolish
- Will not work if fired too quickly
- Cannot equip for 5 seconds after accessing a Radial Menu

items.name: SS Light Setter
items.description:
Allows you to change the light settings of multi-lamps from a distance.

Right click will save light settings, allowing you to apply them to other lights quickly. Right click again to clear saved settings.

items.name: SS Model Selector
items.description:
Allows you to pick the model of glass items from a distance.

Right click while facing a structure to set its model to the gun, subsequent shots will then apply that model. Right click again to clear.

items.name: SS Repair Gun
items.description: Repair items by shooting them!

items.name: SS Transfer Gun
items.description: Right click to set a source, left click to transfer to your target. G will set yourself as the source. Holding left shift will transfer only the first item Left Alt will transfer the first item only to you.

items.name: SS Transfer Tool
items.description: Allows you to transfer items from anything with an inventory to anything with an inventory remotely.

items.name: SS Transparency Cycler
items.description:
Allows you to change the transparency of glass items from a distance.

Right click while facing a structure to save its settings, subsequent shots will apply those settings. Right click again to clear.

items.name: SS Turret Configurator
items.description:
- Shoot a turret to open its config menu
- Right click to copy settings (Left click to apply those settings)

items.name: SS Spray Painter
items.description:
Apply a dye to this, then shoot it at structures to paint them. 

Shoots a long distance, doesn't consume dye.

Note: color doesn't update in singleplayer until restart.

items.name: SS Underwater Tool
items.description:
- Has 5 modes (open, close, freeze, lock sides, unlock sides)
- Right click to toggle mode

Note: You can't freeze an open port hole and you can't open a frozen one(you need to close first)

items.name: SS Visibility Tool
items.description:
Can hide or show all hideable structures that belong to your tribe in a large area.

When used by an admin, it will hide or show for all tribes.

items.description:

- More powerful, bigger range & thinner model.
- Can snap to itself(Press G to disable)

items.name: SS Ammo Box
items.description: Deployable device to supply ammunition to nearby turrets.

- Can distribute Owl Pellets to nearby Gachas

- Can use Tek Generator or any Kibble for fuel (will automatically use fuel if no power is available)

items.name: SS Auto Crafter
items.description:
Place another crafting station inside and this will automatically craft any recipe selected from the inserted crafting station.

**Requires Tek Gen & does not give crafting exp**

items.name: Selected Recipe
items.description: Using Pull Selected on this item will pull resources for the selected recipe.

items.name: SS Auto Turret
items.description: Has advanced targeting settings.

items.name: SS Ballista Turret
items.description:
Fires massive arrows which knockback hit enemies.

Uses Spear Bolts for ammo.

items.name: SS Cannon Turret
items.description: Fires cannon balls at things.

items.name: SS Flame Turret
items.description:
Spews fire at things. Will cause riders to dismount and unmounted dinos to flee.

Uses Flamethrower Ammo. (note: ignore targeting range, it has a set range regardless of setting)

items.name: SS Heavy Auto Turret
items.description: Requires electricity to run. Provides increased firepower, but consumes FOUR bullets while firing.  Can be configured to automatically attack hostiles within range.

items.name: SS Laser Turret
items.description:
Fires an energy beam! Doesn't do as much damage as other turrets but slows enemies and has a chance to blind them.

Uses Gasoline as Ammo.

items.name: SS Minigun Turret
items.description: Uses Advanced Sniper Ammo.

items.name: SS Plant Species X Seed
items.description: - Has advanced targeting features.

items.name: SS Plant Species X Seed
items.description:
- Has advanced targeting features.

- CHEAT version

items.name: SS Rocket Turret
items.description:
Fires rockets at things.

Note: Has a much higher targeting range than other turrets but will not target anything within 10 foundations of itself.

items.name: SS Tek Turret
items.description:
Requires Tek Generator power.  Consumes Element Shards while firing.  Has a variety of smart-targeting configuration options.

- Lockable & Pin-codeable

items.name: SS Tranq Turret
items.description:
Tranquilizes things. Doesn't do any damage, will not target unconcious things.

Uses Shocking Tranquilizer Darts.

items.name: SS Simple Bed
items.description:
Thatch may not make the most comfortable mattress, but this bed acts as a respawn point for you and your tribe.

- Snaps to each other(Press G to disable)

items.name: SS Bunk Bed
items.description:
This modern bunk-style bed has two mattresses, and a high thread count.  Acts as a respawn point for you and your tribe with half cooldown time.

- Snaps to each other(Press G to disable)

items.name: SS Tek Sleeping Pod
items.description:
This Tek-powered Chamber lets you rapidly recover vitals, and slowly gain XP even when sleeping. You can also sleep soundly within it, protected even while on a moving platform!

- Snaps to each other(Press G to disable)

items.name: SS Domesticated Bee Hive
items.description:
This is an exceptionally friendly bee hive! 

Produces honey and waters nearby crops.

items.name: SS Blueprint Maker
items.description: Converts Structures to Blueprints

items.name: SS Charge Injector
items.description:
Keeps the Nameless at bay by injecting charge directly into the ground.

- Adjustable range (charge usage increases exponentially with radius)

items.name: SS Charge Station
items.description:
Will draw charge from nearby light pets(note: only receives 1 charge for every 5 pulled).

Can re-charge Charge Batteries. 

Does not protect against nameless and can not craft element.

items.name: SS Cloning Chamber
items.description:
Enables you to generate clones of your creatures!

- Keeps imprinting & level ups

items.name: SS Converter
items.description: Converts vanilla structures & blueprints to their SS counterpart and vice versa.

items.name: SS Cryofridge
items.description:
Requires electricity to run.  Keeps Cryopods alive forever!

- Can snap to itself(Press G to disable)

items.name: SS Crystal Cracker
items.description:
Automatically opens Gacha crystals placed inside.

Can upload to dedicated storage on demand.

items.name: SS Dedicated Chip
items.description:
Dropped from an SS Dedicated Storage. Digital integrity decays over time. Re-deposit this into an SS Dedicated Storage to get the resources out.

Cannot be uploaded.

items.name: SS Dedicated Storage
items.description:
Holds an immense amount of a single resource.

Can hit to deposit. (doesn't work on PvE, no friendly fire)

When powered(tek gen), acts as a fridge.

items.name: SS Dedicated Storage Intake
items.description:
Will take items from you or your dino that have associated nearby dedicated storage units.

Can be upgraded in size. (does not change distribution range)

items.name: SS Dino Uplink
items.description:
Automatically sends items from your dino to nearby SS Dedicated Storages.

Self-sustaining. Does not require power.

items.name: SS Drone Terminal
items.description: Crafts scouts & enforcers.

items.name: SS Dyeria
items.description:
Can make all types of dyes.

Doesn't need a water source.

items.name: Element
items.description:
A strange, highly advanced material humming with energy. It dissolves when transferred across ARKs.
Requires Full Batteries to craft!

items.name: SS Element Catalyzer
items.description:
Crafts element but requires direct contact with liquid Element to function.

- Recipe is the same as at a Charge Node except there is no cooldown.

items.name: SS Elevator Call Button
items.description:
Will call the nearest elevator to your position.

If unlocked, then anybody can use it.

items.name: SS Large Elevator Platform
items.description:
Attach to an Elevator Track to carry a Large amount of Weight.

5 foundations wide and 3 foundation long.

items.name: SS Medium Elevator Platform
items.description:
Attach to an Elevator Track to carry a Medium amount of Weight.

3 foundations wide and 2 foundation long.

items.name: SS Small Elevator Platform
items.description:
Attach to an Elevator Track to carry a Small amount of Weight.

Size of 1 foundation.

items.name: SS Small Elevator Track
items.description:
Attach an Elevator Platform to these to complete an Elevator!

1 wall high.

items.name: SS Farmer
items.description:
- Distributes fertilizer to nearby crop plots.
- Will collect fertilizer from nearby compost bins and dung beetles.
- Can use Tek Generator or Calien Soup for fuel (will automatically use fuel if no power is available)

items.name: SS Feeding Trough
items.description:
Feeds nearby dinos.

Note: blocks resource & dino spawns in its feeding range

items.name: SS Tek Trough
items.description:
Put food for your nearby pets in this, and they'll automatically eat it when hungry! Can refridgerate items, so long as it's powered by a Tek Generator!

Note: blocks resource & dino spawns in its feeding range

items.name: SS Tek Shield Generator
items.description:
Generates an impenetrable, expandable spherical shield to keep out enemies. 

- Can use Tek Generator or Element(will automatically use element if no power is available)
- Can be placed on rafts & saddles
- Protects against Aberration radiation

items.name: SS Refrigerator
items.description:
Requires electricity to run.  Keeps perishables from spoiling for a long time.

- Can snap to itself(Press G to disable)

items.name: SS Gacha Gavager
items.description:
Force feeds one gacha.

Gachas fed this way are not saddened by being close to other gachas.

items.name: SS Gardener
items.description:
- Collects crops from nearby crop plots.
- Auto harvests Plant Species R (server owner can disable)
- Can place preserving salt in inventory.
- Can use Tek Generator or Beer for fuel (will automatically use fuel if no power is available)

items.name: SS Tek Gas Collector
items.description:
Place on a Gas Vent to extract Congealed Gas Balls over time.

- Will automatically send full stacks of gas balls to any dedicated storage units that are set to accept gas balls.
- Does not detoriate over time.

items.name: SS Electrical Generator
items.description:
- Silent
- Snaps to foundations (4 ways)
- Can be pin coded & locked

items.name: SS Tek Generator
items.description:
Powers nearby structures wirelessly!

- Can be placed on saddles & rafts (only powers structures on the same saddle or raft, conversely generators not placed on a saddle or raft will not power structures on saddles or rafts)

items.name: SS Wind Turbine
items.description: - Snaps to foundations and ceilings.

items.name: SS Mutator
items.description: Unleashes the full power of element to alter dinos in powerful ways.

items.name: SS Hatchery
items.description:
- Collects fertilized eggs (won't pick up eggs at or below 1% incubation)
- Incubates eggs in its inventory (only incubates to 1%)
- Boosts egg production of nearby dinos
- Can auto send specific dino eggs to nearby SS Egg Incubators
- Can use Tek Generator or Re-Fertilizer for fuel (will automatically use fuel if no power is available)

items.name: SS Hitching Post
items.description: Allows nearby dinos to be hitched, preventing them from moving even when set to wander.

items.name: SS Tek Hitching Post
items.description: Allows nearby dinos to be hitched, preventing them from moving even when set to wander.

items.name: Unassembled SS TEK Hover Skiff
items.description:
Craft this item to receive a new SS TEK Hover Skiff.

- Crafts the item instead of spawning it
- Can be picked up (server admin can disable)
- Holds 10x more fuel (including alternate fuels)

items.name: SS Incinerator
items.description: Destroys anything placed in its inventory.

items.name: SS Egg Incubator
items.description:
Deployable device for warming and monitoring up to ten eggs at once. Requires electricity to run.

Automatically sets the median temperature based on all eggs in the incubator. Can auto-hatch and select eggs with wanted stats if enabled (can be disabled by server admin).

Can snap to foundations, ceilings, and roofs. "G" to toggle snapping.

items.name: SS Industrial Cooker
items.description:
- Can pin code.

- Can use electricity or gas for fuel (will automatically use gas if no power is available)

items.name: SS Industrial Forge
items.description:
- Can pin code.
- Can use electricity or gas for fuel (will automatically use gas if no power is available)
- Snaps to itself for perfect alignment.
- Press G to disable snapping.

items.name: SS Industrial Grill
items.description:
- Can pin code.

- Can use electricity or gas for fuel (will automatically use gas if no power is available)

items.name: SS Industrial Grinder
items.description:
Grind up crafted items and certain resources!

- Can use electricity or gas for fuel (will automatically use gas if no power is available)

items.name: Ambergris
items.description: A waxy substance secreted by the Astrocetus. Used to create ordnance for the Astrocetus Tek Saddle.

items.name: Ammonite Bile
items.description: A congealed glob of Ammonite Bile. Can be used for medicinal purposes when carefully prepared.

items.name: Bio Toxin
items.description: Powerful toxin harvested from an organism.

items.name: Chitin
items.description: This firm, flexible material makes up exoskeletons. Hacked primarily from dead insects.

items.name: Clay
items.description: Created by grinding Sand with Cactus Sap.

items.name: Crystal
items.description: **THE TOOLTIP IS INCORRECT, WILL USE ANY 2 GEMS(red, blue or green)**

items.name: Element Dust
items.description: A small pile of Dust that could be refined into Element or Element Shards.

items.name: Fiber
items.description: Delicately collected strands of plant.  Perfect for making thread, cloth, or rope.

items.name: Flint
items.description: Ferroceric flint that holds an edge better than regular stone.

items.name: Fungal Wood
items.description: A thick, sturdy cutting from a huge mushroom. Has all of the properties of a chunk of wood!

items.name: Congealed Gas Ball
items.description: Used for crafting, can be found within Gas Veins.

items.name: Blue Gem
items.description: This strange Gem has unusual properties that makes it ideal for increasing the structural integrity of items, armor, and structures.

items.name: Green Gem
items.description: This strange Gem is used as a crafting ingredient in primitive tools and saddles.

items.name: Red Gem
items.description: This strange Gem has many unique properties that make it ideal for crafting.

items.name: Preserving Salt
items.description: Created by grinding salt with sulfur. Preserves food.

items.name: Propellant
items.description: Used to manufacture highly flammable substances.

items.name: Raw Prime Fish Meat
items.description: Eating raw food will SLIGHTLY sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  This excellent cut spoils very quickly. Most wild carnivores love this meat.

items.name: Raw Prime Meat
items.description:
Eating raw food will sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  This excellent cut spoils very quickly.
Most wild carnivores love this meat.

items.name: Raw Salt
items.description: Mix it with sulfur to obtain Preserving Salt.

items.name: Sand
items.description: Used to craft Clay. Can be found in Sand rocks

items.name: Cactus Sap
items.description: Cut of cactus that giving sap and when it is consumed hydrates your body

items.name: Sap
items.description: A thick blob of unrefined sap.

items.name: Silk
items.description: Obtained from the Moth creatures. Used to craft desert clothes and the tent.

items.name: Spoiled Meat
items.description:
Eww... do not eat.
This must have a use, right?

items.name: Spoiled Meat
items.description:
Eww... do not eat.

items.name: Sulfur
items.description: Used to craft distinct kind of ammunition. Can be found in the Caves

items.name: Thatch
items.description: Sticks torn from trees.  Useful for primitive bindings.

items.name: Shell Fragment
items.description: A firm, flexible material from the shell of a Megachelon. Can be used as a replacement for Keratin.

items.name: SS Item Collector
items.description:
- Collects dropped items(poop, achatina paste, unfertilized eggs, pearls, gacha crystals & owl pellets) & poop produced in Vivariums. Also collects metal from dedicated storages and ingots from forges
- Distributes poop to Compost Bins & Dung Beetles, crystals to Crystal Crackers, pellets to Animal Tenders, metal to forges, and ingots to dedicated storages
- Can use Tek Generator or Gasoline for fuel (will automatically use fuel if no power is available).

items.name: SS Item Translocator
items.description: Can send items instantly to other item translocators.

items.name: SS Tek Leash
items.description:
Electronic leash to keep your dinos from wandering too far.

Doesn't require power.

items.name: SS Tek Light
items.description: Useful for spelunking, they can be attached to any surface, self powered by Element Shards , or linked to generators, and picked-up after placement.

items.name: SS Loadout Mannequin
items.description:
Deployable device to store and display Equipment and current damage state.

Can snap to foundations, ceilings, and roofs. "G" to toggle snapping. 

Can install refrigeration. Tek Fridges provide 4x Fridge spoil rates.

items.name: SS Mannequin
items.description: A posable character that you can dress up.

items.name: SS Multi Lamp
items.description:
- Can place on floors, walls and ceilings
- Can set color and secondary color(will pulsate between the two colors)
- Automatically turns on at dusk and off at dawn

items.name: SS Nanny
items.description:
- Gives food to nearby babies (under 15%)
- Imprints nearby non-adult dinos
- Can place preserving salt in inventory.
- Can use Tek Generator or Honey for fuel 
(will automatically use fuel if no power is available)

items.name: SS Noglin Nullifier
items.description:
This structure emits a poison that causes noglins to get knocked off their host and become targetable by turrets for a short time. Fueled by Congealed Gas Balls.

<RichColor Color="1, .3, .4, 1">Requires Noglin Dermis to Craft!</>

items.name: SS Electrical Outlet
items.description:
- Can be hidden.
- Can hide all connecting wires (thin grey ones).
- Can hide sparks effect.

items.name: SS Planetary Shield
items.description:
Protects the planet from meteors.

** Requires power from at least 4 tek generators to function. **

items.name: SS Pressure Plate
items.description:
A mechanical trigger that activates nearby devices and structures when stepped on.

-Can disguise as other ceilings
-Same snap points as ceilings, not treated as a floor

items.name: SS Repair Station
items.description:
Automatically repairs armor and weapons placed inside.

Requires resources for repair to also be in the repair station.

items.name: SS Sheep Herder
items.description:
- Shears nearby sheep.
- Can place preserving salt in inventory.
- Can use Tek Generator or Raw Meat for fuel (will automatically use fuel if no power is available)

items.name: SS Shield Post
items.description:
Connects together to generate an impenetrable shield fence to keep out enemies. 

-Requires Tek Generator for fuel

items.name: SS Metal Spike Wall
items.description:
These incredibly sharp metal spikes are dangerous to any that touch them.

- Snap like fence foundations(press G to disable snapping)

items.name: SS Wooden Spike Wall
items.description:
These incredibly sharp wooden stakes are dangerous to any that touch them.

- Can snap like fence foundations(press G to disable snapping)

items.name: SS Bookshelf
items.description:
A large reinforced bookshelf to store blueprints, notes, and other small trinkets in.

- Metal Stength
- Can snap to itself(Press G to disable)

items.name: SS Large Storage Box
items.description:
A large cabinet to store goods in.

- Snaps to itself for perfect alignment.
- Press G to disable snapping.

items.name: SS Metal Storage Box
items.description:
A large metal chest to store goods in.

- Snaps to itself for perfect alignment.
- Press G to disable snapping.

items.name: SS Storage Box
items.description:
A small box to store goods in.

- Snaps to itself for perfect alignment.
- Press G to disable snapping.

items.name: SS Tek Storage
items.description:
Similar size to dedicated storage but holds less of anything.

When powered(tek gen), acts as a fridge.

items.name: SS Large Taxidermy Base
items.description:
Place a harvested dermis to show off your prowess!

Has multiple bases and snaps to foundations & ceilings.

items.name: SS Medium Taxidermy Base
items.description:
Place a harvested dermis to show off your prowess!

items.name: SS Tek Bridge
items.description: Extendable force bridge

items.name: SS Laboratory
items.description:
Functions as a chemistry bench, can do resource conversions and make fertilizer.

Chemistry bench recipes output is doubled.

Requires a Tek Gen for power.

items.name: Flamethrower Ammo
items.description: Fuel for the flamethrower.

items.name: Bug Repellant
items.description: This gnarly paste makes you nearly invisible to bugs, bats, and spiders. Just don't attack them or get too close, and they'll ignore you! Effect lasts 10 minutes.

items.name: Lesser Antidote
items.description: Cures Lesser Afflictions!

items.name: Fertilizer
items.description: High nitrogen fertilizer that helps crops grow in their plots.

items.name: Mutagel
items.description:
Rare mechanochemical substance. Use with caution to tame autonomous Stryders.

This alternate recipe utilizes advanced techniques to craft Mutagel.

items.name: Mutagen
items.description:
Rare substance with aggravating and mutagentic properties. Use with caution to boost creature stats and gain access to Rockwell's Inner Sanctum.

This alternate recipe utilizes advanced techniques to craft Mutagen.

items.name: Narcotic
items.description: Increases your health, but puts you to sleep.

items.name: Stimulant
items.description: Keeps you awake, but dehydrates you.

items.name: Cementing Paste
items.description: This thick, waterproof paste could be used as mortar, or to thicken another substance.

items.name: Clay
items.description: Created by grinding Sand with Cactus Sap in a Mortar and Pestle.

items.name: Gasoline (Gas-Crafted)
items.description: An advanced fuel, created from compressed natural gas. Can only be used in machines designed to consume it.

items.name: Gunpowder
items.description: An powerful propellant. Necessary for any firearm or explosive.

items.name: Preserving Salt
items.description: Created by grinding salt with sulfur in a Mortar and Pestle. Preserves food.

items.name: Primal Crystal
items.description: This strange crystalline material can be shaped into lenses, used as an electronics component, or mixed into powerful explosives. This particular crystal pulses with primal energy and is the Crystal Wyvern's favorite treat.

items.name: Propellant
items.description: Used to manufacture highly flammable substances.

items.name: Sparkpowder
items.description: Created by grinding flint with stone in a Mortar and Pestle or Chemistry Table.

items.name: Absorbent Substrate
items.description: This sticky compound excels at absorbing other chemicals.

items.name: SS Tek Cooking Pot
items.description:
Can make advanced recipes, kibble & beer. Produces twice the output of each recipe.

Accepts water like a crop plot(ie from nearby taps). Requires a Tek Gen for power.

items.name: SS Beer
items.description: Doesn't require a water jar to craft and doesn't return a water on use.

items.name: SS Tek Forge
items.description:
Instantly smelts metal into ingots, wood into charcoal, organic polymer into polymer & condensed gas into gas balls.

Only requires 1 metal per ingot.

items.name: Element Dust
items.description: A small pile of Dust that could be refined into Element or Element Shards.

items.name: Element
items.description: A strange, highly advanced material humming with energy. It dissolves when transferred across ARKs.

items.name: Element
items.description: A strange, highly advanced material humming with energy. It dissolves when transferred across ARKs.

items.name: Element Shard
items.description: A small chunk of strange, highly advanced material. It dissolves when transferred across ARKs.

items.name: Gasoline
items.description: An advanced fuel. Can only be used in machines designed to consume it.

items.name: SS Tek Refrigerator
items.description: Can fill water containers & resets the spoil timer of items placed inside.

items.name: Iced Canteen
items.description: Safely carries a sizable amount of water, and is reasonably lightweight. Cools you down when drinking from it!

items.name: Iced Water Jar
items.description: Safely carries a lot of water, but is also a bit heavy. Cools you down when drinking from it!

items.name: SS Tek Jump Pad
items.description:
A Tek-powered propulsion device; useful for traversal and mayhem.

-Snaps to foundations, ceilings, and roofs ("G" to disable)

items.name: SS Tek Sensor
items.description: An advanced detection and activation system used to automate nearby devices and structures. Requires Tek Generator power.

items.name: SS Tek Stove
items.description:
Cooks meat instantly and can make jerky.

Requires Tek Gen for power.

items.name: Cooked Meat Jerky
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  Lasts longer than cooked meat.
Wild carnivores will eat it, but prefer raw meat.

items.name: Prime Meat Jerky
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  More effective than normal meat jerky, and lasts longer than cooked prime meat.
Wild carnivores like this meat a lot.

items.name: SS Teleporter
items.description:
Allows instantaneous traversal between Teleporters! 

- Requires Tek Generator to power.
- Teleport radius can be adjusted via radial menu.
- Can be placed on saddles & rafts.

items.name: SS Standing Torch
items.description:
A torch on a tall piece of wood that lights and warms the immediate area.

- Doesn't require fuel.
- Place dye in inventory to change color.

items.name: SS Wall Torch
items.description:
A torch on a metal connector that lights and warms the immediate area. Must be placed on a wall.

- Doesn't require fuel.
- Can change color with dye.

items.name: SS Tek Transmitter
items.description:
Transmits items, Survivors, and creatures to other ARKs!

- Can teleport to boss arenas
- Can scan all dinos on the ARK and display their position & level.

items.name: SS Tree Sap Tap
items.description:
- Larger inventory
- More reliable sap production

items.name: SS Artifact Pedestal

Has multiple structure base variants to choose from.

Press "G" to disable snapping.

items.name: SS Trophy Wall-Mount

- Press G to disable snapping.

items.name: SS Vessel

Dinos will lose all items when put inside the vivarium.

**Requires Tek Gen for egg/poop collection**
